HEADWORD: Psychrometer
<hw>Psy*chrom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>psychro`s</grk> cold + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>psychrom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring
the tension of the aqueous vapor in the atmosphere, being essentially a
wet and dry bulb hygrometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Psychrometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
